cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces an extension of temporal logic to express hyperproperties.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as hyperproperties are important in security and coding theory.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the correctness of computer programs.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses model checking for temporal logic with path quantification.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the model checking problem.
